<HEADLINE> United Scrapes By With Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BLACKBURN, England (AP) -- Manchester United played a scoreless  
tie against Blackburn on Wednesday night, putting it on track to 
clinch the English Premier League title Sunday -- the final day of 
the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Manchester United (21-3-12) has 76 points, one more than Arsenal  
(21-4-12), which lost 1-0 at Leeds on Tuesday. Manchester United 
plays at home Sunday against Derby while Arsenal plays at home that 
same day against Aston Villa. 
</P>
<P>
	Manchester United is trying for an unprecedented English triple  
and will play later this month in the finals of The Football 
Association Cup and the European Champions Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackburn (7-17-13), which won the Premier League in 1995, was  
assured of relegation to the first division with the loss. 
</P>
</TEXT>
