<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Police Kill Knife-Wielding Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. CLOUD, Minn. (AP) -- Police shot and killed a man after he  
yanked a bloody knife out of his chest and charged at officers with 
it. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers responded Tuesday night to a call from a neighbor who  
said Kevin Hartwig showed up on his doorstep covered in blood and 
carrying a Bible. The neighbor told police that Hartwig, 33, said 
he had sacrificed his dog and that God made him do it. 
</P>
<P>
	Hartwig then returned to his home. When officers arrived,  
Hartwig came outside with the knife sticking out of his chest. 
Officers believe Hartwig had stabbed himself. 
</P>
<P>
	Police told him to leave the knife in his chest while waiting  
for an ambulance, but he pulled it out and charged ``in a rage,'' 
Capt. Len Smallwood said. 
</P>
<P>
	An officer fired and shot Hartwig in the chest, police said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
