<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 28, Nasdaq Climbs 17 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened mixed. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is down 28 points in today's early going. Losers 
on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 6-5 lead over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 17 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is down one point. 
</P>
<P>
	The high-techs are getting a bit of a boost from Cisco Systems,  
after the company released better-than-expected earnings. 
</P>
<P>
	The maker of computer networking products also announced a  
2-for-1 stock split. 
</P>
<P>
	In the mergers and acquisitions arena, Cox Communications has  
agreed to buy TCA Cable, while USA Networks and Lycos have halted 
merger plans. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar is higher against the euro and the yen, amid today's  
government upheaval in Moscow. 
</P>
<P>
	The firing of the Russian prime minister also sent Russian share  
prices and the ruble sharply lower. 

</P>
</TEXT>
