<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-12 14:54:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Mostly Up; Flat Vs. Yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The dollar was flat against the Japanese yen  
Wednesday after nearly recouping losses caused by the turmoil 
surrounding the resignation of Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar rose against the euro and other major currencies as  
the U.S. currency became a safe haven after Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin fired Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov, damaging immediate 
prospects for peace in Yugoslavia. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0653 in late trading in New York, down  
from $1.0715 late Tuesday. The dollar edged lower to 120.95 
Japanese yen from 120.97 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar rallied Wednesday morning as interest rates rose,  
giving traders reason to buy bonds and dollars, then weakened after 
the announcement that Rubin was leaving the Clinton administration. 
Rubin is widely considered the architect of the Clinton 
administration strategy that has helped the eight-year Wall Street 
boom. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had the enormous amount of volatility on Rubin's  
resignation and then that gave way to a dollar selloff, which 
negated the earlier dollar rally,'' said Dan Bernzweig, a foreign 
exchange trader at Bank Leumi USA. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones industrials fell as much as 213 points on the news  
before recovering to finish down about 27 points at the close. Bond 
prices fell before rising in the late afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	The market recovery was helped by news that Rubin's deputy,  
Lawrence Summers, would be nominated to replace the departing 
secretary. 
</P>
<P>
	``The expectation is that Summers will be a nice replacement,''  
Bernzweig said. ``Although Rubin has done a very good job, (his 
leaving) is not going to damage the U.S. dollar.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, the euro lost its fight Wednesday against the dollar  
as Yeltsin dumped his prime minister and Cabinet for the third time 
in a bit more than a year. 
</P>
<P>
	Yeltsin also announced that Russia would halt its attempted  
mediation of the Kosovo crisis if its proposals were not heeded. 
NATO has been bombing Yugoslavia since late March. Europe is 
expected to bear the brunt of rebuilding the area once hostilities 
stop; the euro is the new currency of 11 European nations. 
</P>
<P>
	``The good efforts toward peace, which gave stability and  
strength to the euro, are now more remote,'' Bernzweig said. 
</P>
<P>
	In other trading, the dollar was quoted at 1.5056 Swiss francs,  
up from 1.5016, and 1.4592 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4530. The 
British pound fell to $1.6176 from $1.6234. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed rate. 
</P>
<P>
	Based on the euro's exchange rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8359  
German marks, up from 1.8255; 6.1576 French francs, up from 6.1237; 
and 1,818.18 Italian lire, up from 1,808.32. 
</P>
</TEXT>
