<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0683, up from $1.0585 Tuesday. The  
dollar was quoted at 121.29 Japanese yen, up from 121.02 yen. At 
midday in New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0661 and the dollar 
was quoted at 120.88 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Tuesday: 1.5014 Swiss  
francs, down from 1.5201; 1.4578 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4500. 
The British pound was quoted at $1.6204, up from $1.6162. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8308 German marks, down from 1.8477; 
6.1402 French francs, down from 6.1970; 2.0628 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0819; 1,812.48 Italian lire, down from 1,829.26. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $276.60 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$279.00 on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $276.95, down from $278.36.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.15 in Hong Kong to close at $285.85.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.35 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.40. 
</P>
</TEXT>
