<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Memphis Hospital Announces Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- St. Jude Children's Research Hospital  
announced a $1 billion expansion plan Wednesday that will allow its 
scientists to research rare genetic and infectious diseases. 
</P>
<P>
	With the expansion, to be completed in six or seven years, the  
hospital will add the Children's Infection Defense Center and the 
Pediatric Genetic Diseases Center. 
</P>
<P>
	The infection center, while continuing the hospital's work on  
bone marrow transplantation, will focus on finding vaccines and new 
therapies for such diseases as AIDS, pneumonia, tuberculosis and 
cholera. 
</P>
<P>
	The other new center will search for genetic causes and  
treatments for problems such as sickle cell anemia, brittle bone 
disease, hemophilia and inherited immune deficiencies. 
</P>
<P>
	St. Jude patients are admitted regardless of their ability to  
pay. Richard Shadyac, executive director of St. Jude's fund-raising 
arm, said the hospital has already raised a good portion of the $1 
billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
