<HEADLINE> Kenya Ambassador Moving to Guatemala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton said Wednesday he is  
nominating Prudence Bushnell, the ambassador and Africa expert 
wounded when terrorists bombed the U.S. Embassy in Kenya, to be 
U.S. ambassador to Guatemala. 
</P>
<P>
	Bushnell, a career diplomat with 11 years' experience working in  
Africa or on Africa issues, must be confirmed by the Senate. 
</P>
<P>
	She served in Senegal and India before taking over as U.S.  
ambassador to Kenya in August 1996. Bushnell was among 5,000 people 
wounded last Aug. 7 when a bomb exploded at the embassy in downtown 
Nairobi, killing 213 people, including 12 Americans. 
</P>
