	Mets Beat Rockies 10-5  
</P>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Edgardo Alfonzo homered and drove in four runs and  
Robin Ventura had three RBIs, powering the New York Mets past the 
Colorado Rockies 10-5 today. Roger Cedeno had four hits and scored 
three runs for the Mets, who averted being swept in the three-game 
series. Rick Reed (3-1) allowed four runs and eight hits in five 
innings. 

</P>
