<HEADLINE> Pearl Jam Helping Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Pearl Jam is putting out a single and donating  
all proceeds to Kosovo refugees. 
</P>
<P>
	The song, ``Last Kiss,'' is to be released June 8. The proceeds  
will go to CARE, an Atlanta-based relief agency. 
</P>
<P>
	Once Pearl Jam's new album, ``No Boundaries,'' is released a  
week later, Epic Records plans to make a $1 million contribution to 
CARE and two other aid agencies, CARE said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Pearl Jam is proud to offer this small contribution to help  
improve the appalling conditions of the refugees suffering from 
this human rights tragedy in Kosovo,'' said Kelly Curtis, Pearl 
Jam's manager. 
</P>
<P>
	``Last Kiss'' is a remake of the 1964 hit by J. Frank Wilson &AMP;  
the Cavaliers. It's the first single from Pearl Jam's new album. 
</P>
