<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Has Third Foot Removed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WHITTIER, Calif. (AP) -- Jose Maria Lopez spent most of his 33  
years hiding a third foot that protruded from his left ankle. He 
would cut his shoe at the heel and wear baggy pants to cover the 
6-inch appendage. 
</P>
<P>
	Because the foot was inside his left leg, Lopez had to swing his  
right leg around the growth to avoid hitting it when he walked. 
</P>
<P>
	He now has just two feet, thanks to a surgeon who teamed up with  
Whittier Hospital Medical Center to amputate the defect free of 
charge. 
</P>
<P>
	``It has changed my life completely and I'm feeling fantastic,''  
said Lopez, a stable hand who wants to be a horse trainer. ``For a 
long time I've wanted to buy boots and now I can do it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lopez, who works as a hot-walker at Santa Anita Park, cooling  
down horses that have just run, was born in Mexico, where a doctor 
told his family the extra foot was a bad omen from God and his leg 
would have to be amputated at the hip. He learned to live with the 
foot instead. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Michael O'Shea removed the foot -- which had a fully  
developed ankle, a heel and four toes -- during a 70-minute 
operation in February. 
</P>
<P>
	The cast came off four weeks later. Lopez said it is still  
strange walking around without the foot. 
</P>
<P>
	``Sometimes I think I have it and I swing my leg out and I say,  
`Oh I don't have it,''' he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
