<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lakers Set To Eliminate Rockets  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- The Houston Rockets have been in this spot  
before, and the Los Angeles Lakers know it. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not over yet, we realize that,'' Glen Rice said.  
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers routed the Rockets 110-98 to take a 2-0 lead Tuesday  
in their best-of-5 series. 
</P>
<P>
	But the Rockets have an 11-4 record in playoff elimination games  
under coach Rudy Tomjanovich. Their next test comes in Game 3 
Thursday night at Compaq Center. 
</P>
<P>
	``We feel that we still haven't done anything,'' Rice said.  
``It's going to be a dog fight in Houston. I'm sure their fans are 
going to be behind them 110 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	``Right now, they realize that their backs are against the wall,  
so they are going to come out fighting. 
</P>
<P>
	Houston's resiliency is well documented. In their championship  
years of 1994 and 1995, they were down 2-0 each year to the Phoenix 
Suns in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
	But those comebacks were in best-of-7 series. The Rockets have  
no margin for error this time. 
</P>
<P>
	Should the Rockets add to their comeback history, they would be  
the sixth team in NBA history to recover from an 0-2 start in a 
best-of-5 series. Denver did it most recently against Seattle in 
1994. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're not going to panic. I've been in worse situations than  
this,'' Charles Barkley said. ``We just got to go home and win, 
plain and simple. They did what they had to do. That's what home 
court is all about. We just got to go home and win one and then win 
two.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockets are looking more to Game 1 for inspiration. Two late  
defensive plays by the Lakers helped them to a 101-100 victory. 
</P>
<P>
	``Game 1 is a lot more indicative of how well we can play  
against this team,'' Barkley said. ``That was a costly loss, but 
this was just a blowout.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers have won six games in a row, including their last  
four games of the regular season. In fact, the Rockets are the last 
team to beat the Lakers. 
</P>
<P>
	``We feel that when we go out there together and play aggressive  
defense and stop them from doing the things that they want to do, 
the sky is the limit,'' Rice said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers again showed defensive power in Game 2. They allowed  
the Rockets only 12 first-quarter points. Hakeem Olajuwon and 
Scottie Pippen were not factors. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley and the bench had to fight alone. Sam Mack scored 20  
points and Brent Price added 18 points off the bench. Barkley had 
19 points and 13 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've got to go back and regroup,'' Tomjanovich said. ``The  
biggest adjustment is to come out and play. I just need to go back 
and look at everything. It will be a hard one to watch. We just 
need to bounce back.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers added 3-point shooting to their defensive punch in  
Game 2 and never gave the Rockets a chance. The Lakers hit 10-of-18 
from beyond the arc and Derek Fisher followed his playoff career 
high of 20 points in Game 1 with 16 in Game 2. He was 4-for-6 
shooting 3-pointers Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``We can't focus on what they are doing and how they're  
feeling,'' Kobe Bryant said. ``We have to focus on this ball club 
and what our potential is and what we're capable of doing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers have a bit of playoff history going , too. The  
Rockets are 5-17 in playoff series when they lose the first game. 
The Lakers have swept their first-round opponent seven times, 
including the Rockets in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles is 7-5 when taking a 2-0 lead in best-of-5 series.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
