<HEADLINE> Eighth Body Recovered From Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HAUULA, Hawaii (AP) -- Geologists examining the aftermath of a  
fatal lands7lide at a popular waterfall found the body of an eighth 
victim on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The body is believed to be that of Sara Johnson, 24, a  
California woman who is the only person still missing since 
Sunday's slide. Boulders and rocks crashed down 600 feet onto 
dozens of people lounging around a pool at the base of a waterfall 
in Sacred Falls State Park on Oahu. 
</P>
<P>
	State geologists checking the safety of the area located the  
body at the edge of a pool that sits below the 90-foot waterfall. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Johnson's boyfriend and 11 other people remained  
hospitalized Wednesday from injuries suffered in the landslide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
