<HEADLINE> Injured Arena Official Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Ed Manning, an Arena Football League  
official injured earlier this month when a player ran into him, was 
moved Tuesday from the intensive care unit and upgraded to fair 
condition. 
</P>
<P>
	Iowa Methodist Medical Center, where Manning has been  
hospitalized since a collision with Iowa's Mike Horacek on May 1, 
said Manning ``continues to improve.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In a statement released through the hospital on Tuesday,  
Manning's family said: ``Ed is growing stronger every day, and his 
condition is improving.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The hospital said Manning was moved out of ICU on Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
