<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Venturi Named U.S. Golf Team Captain  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	IRVING, Texas (AP) -- Ken Venturi, a golf analyst for CBS Sports,  
was selected today as captain of the American team for the 2000 
Presidents Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Venturi, who turns 68 on Saturday, called his selection a dream.  
He follows Jack Nicklaus, Arnold Palmer and Hale Irwin as captains 
of the Presidents Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Venturi has not played on the tour in 30 years, but knows the  
players as well as anyone because of his work with CBS Sports. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will not be a playing captain,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	The Presidents Cup was patterned after the Ryder Cup to give  
foreign players born outside Europe a chance to take part in 
biennial matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990512.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-12 23:52:31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> L.A. County Pushes After-School Care </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Los Angeles County has taken a key step  
toward creating the nation's largest after-school child care 
program to help thousands of ``latchkey'' children. 
</P>
<P>
	The Board of Supervisors got a standing ovation from a group of  
single mothers Tuesday after approving $74 million for free child 
care at 225 elementary schools with large numbers of children from 
families on welfare. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is one of the best gifts that mothers throughout the city  
and the county can get for Mother's Day,'' said Margaret Prescod of 
the Every Mother is a Working Mother Network. ``It's more 
substantial than the flowers we get.'' 
</P>
<P>
	As many as 16,000 children could be enrolled in the program,  
which is funded by federal and state welfare grants. It will begin 
this summer and expand through next year. 
</P>
<P>
	``It should really make life easier for so many people,'' said  
Lynn Bayer, director of the county's welfare department. ``The 
reality is that many of these children don't receive child care and 
go home to empty houses.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Eventually, supervisors said, they hope to increase the funding  
to $120 million and expand it to include older children. 
</P>
<P>
	The program will concentrate on education rather than the  
after-school recreation some districts now offer. While districts 
will work out the details, some concepts include helping children 
with their homework and test preparation, and giving them access to 
computers. 
</P>
<P>
	Affordable child care has been a concern since welfare reforms  
began forcing many recipients to work. The Los Angeles area lags 
behind other urban areas in available child care for poor working 
mothers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
