<HEADLINE> Some Facts About Robert Rubin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAME -- Robert Edward Rubin.  
</P>
<P>
	AGE-BIRTH DATE -- 60. Born Aug. 29, 1938.  
</P>
<P>
	EDUCATION -- Harvard University, A.B., summa cum laude, 1960;  
Yale University Law School, LL.B, 1964. 
</P>
<P>
	EXPERIENCE -- Cleary, Gottlieb, Steen &AMP; Hamilton law firm,  
1964-66; Goldman Sachs &AMP; Co. investment bankers, 1966-1992; 
co-chairman, Goldman Sachs, 1990-92; director of National Economic 
Council in the White House, 1992; Treasury secretary, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	FAMILY -- Wife, Judith Leah Oxenberg, married 1963; children,  
James Samuel and Philip Matthew. 
</P>
<P>
	QUOTE -- ``I am pragmatic and I believe that differences can  
usually be resolved, not always but usually, by being 
straightforward and focusing on substance.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
