<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Parma 3, Olympique Marseille 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- Parma won its third European trophy of the decade,  
beating Olympique Marseille 3-0 Wednesday night in the UEFA Cup 
final on goals by Enrico Chiesa, Hernan Crespo and Paolo Vanoli. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory continued Italian domination of the tournament.  
Parma (1995), Internazionale of Milan (1991, '94, '98), Juventus of 
Turin (1990, '93) and Napoli (1989) have combined to win the UEFA 
Cup eight times in 11 years. 
</P>
<P>
	Parma also won the Cup Winners Cup in 1993 and last week won the  
Italian Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Crespo intercepted a poorly struck header from defender Laurent  
Blanc to goalkeeper Stephane Porato in the 26th minute and scored 
his sixth goal of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten minutes later, Vanoli scored off a cross from Diego Fuser.  
Chiesa added his eighth goal of the tournament in the 55th minute, 
scoring on a 15-yard kick off a cross from Juan Veron. 
</P>
<P>
	Olympique Marseille was missing five regulars: Christophe  
Dugarry, Fabrizio Ravanelli, Peter Luccin and William Gallas were 
suspended; and Eric Roy was hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	Lazio of Rome plays Mallorca next Wednesday at Birmingham,  
England, in the last Cup Winners Cup final. Manchester United plays 
Bayern Munich on May 26 at Barcelona in the Champions Cup final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
