<HEADLINE> Steelers' Bettis Has Appendectomy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Steelers star running back Jerome Bettis  
underwent emergency surgery to remove his appendix following a 
workout. 
</P>
<P>
	Bettis, 27, experienced sudden pain Tuesday while training and  
had the operation at the UCLA Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
	Bettis was recovering at the hospital Wednesday and should be  
ready for Pittsburgh's training camp, which begins July 29 at St. 
Vincent College in Latrobe, Pa., Steelers trainer John Norwig said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bettis has been training with Bob Kersee, who coached the late  
Florence Griffith Joyner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
