<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> SEC Tips To Avoid Internet Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Tips from the Securities and Exchange Commission for avoiding  
Internet investment scams: 
</P>
<P>
	-- Before you invest, check the SEC's EDGAR database at  
www.sec.gov or call your state securities regulator to find out 
whether an investment is legally registered. To locate your state 
regulator, call the North American Securities Administrators 
Association at 202-737-0900 or go to its Web site at www.nasaa.org. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Ask your state regulator whether the person or company selling  
the investment is licensed to do business in your state and whether 
they have a record of complaints or fraud. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Assume that investments offered over the Internet are scams  
until you've done your research and proven otherwise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
