<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kmart, Federated Earnings Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Kmart Corp.'s first-quarter earnings climbed more than 40  
percent from a year ago as affordable prices and wide selection of 
merchandise lured shoppers to its stores. Federated Department 
Stores Inc.'s earnings jumped 48 percent from a year ago, topping 
Wall Street analysts' expectations. 

</P>
<P>
                            *Kmart Corp.    	
</P>
<P>
	The Troy, Mich.-based Kmart earned $67 million, or 14 cents a  
share, for the quarter ended April 28, compared with $47 million, 
or 10 cents a share, in the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales at the nation's third-largest retailer were $8.14 billion,  
up from $7.52 billion last year. Sales at stores open at least a 
year, an industry gauge of performance, rose 6.5 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Kmart's results met Wall Street analysts' expectations.  
</P>
<P>
	``Kmart's performance continues to gain momentum,'' said Kmart  
chairman and president Floyd Hall. ``Comparable sales growth was 
ahead of expectations for the quarter, while total sales increased 
at the highest rate in four years.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Kmart said its 1,377 recently refurbished Big Kmart stores,  
which combine full supermarkets with its discount stores, were 
doing well. Also strong were sales of its private-label merchandise 
lines -- including Martha Stewart home furnishings, and Route 66, 
Jaclyn Smith and Kathy Ireland apparel. 
</P>
<P>
	Kmart, with 2,151 stores, is the nation's No. 3 retailer behind  
Wal-Mart Stores Inc. and Sears, Roebuck &AMP; Co. 

</P>
<P>
                  *Federated Department Stores Inc.    	
</P>
<P>
	The Cincinnati-based retailer earned $87 million, or 40 cents  
per share, in the quarter ended May 1, compared with $60 million, 
or 27 cents per share, for the first 13 weeks last year, Federated 
reported Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales rose to $3.71 billion from $3.46 billion. Sales at stores  
open at least a year, an industry gauge of performance, were up 4 
percent for the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	April was the first month that results from Federated's recent  
acquisition of Fingerhut Companies Inc. were included in its 
financial results. 
</P>
<P>
	Federated is looking to benefit from Fingerhut's expertise in  
handling orders through catalogs and the Internet, in addition to 
database management and direct marketing. 
</P>
<P>
	Federated's results topped Wall Street analysts' estimates. Its  
stock was up $2.25 at $53.25 in morning trading on the New York 
Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Federated operates more than 400 department stores in 33 states  
under the names Bloomingdale's, The Bon Marche, Burdines, 
Goldsmith's, Lazarus, Macy's, Rich's and Stern's. During the first 
quarter, it opened one department store, a Burdines in Tampa, Fla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
