<HEADLINE> Pirates' Meares on Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Pittsburgh Pirates shortstop Pat Meares was put  
on the 15-day disabled list Wednesday because of a tendon problem 
in the pinkie finger of his left hand. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's an old injury, some type of tendon tear,'' Meares said.  
``It's been torn and I've been trying to play with it for three 
weeks. The doctor basically said play with it as long as you can 
until it really bothers you. I have no use of my pinkie and I was 
afraid it was going to affect another finger. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had a lot of pain yesterday when I held the bat. I'm going  
to see a hand specialist tomorrow in Pittsburgh to see if I need 
surgery.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Meares is hitting .297 with no homers and five RBIs in 17 games.  
</P>
<P>
	``Right now we don't know how long he's going to be out,''  
Pittsburgh manager Gene Lamont said. 
</P>
